<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="210" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species large (
<quantity box="[491,614,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" unit="mm" value="19.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="19.0">19–20 mm</quantity>
) and dorsally green. Pronotum and scutellum finely punctured, punctures concolorous. Corium with yellow calloused veins strongly branched (
<figureCitation box="[962,1060,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[262,1368,199,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[196,1390,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–B; Pygoda variegata sp. n. C–D; Pygoda poecila sp. n. E–F; Pygoda irrorata G–H; Pygoda polita I–J; Pygoda ramosa sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460050/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Fig.12A</figureCitation>
). Connexivum completely green without yellow spots or stains; segment VII almost completely black, only basal 1/5 green. Body ventrally pale yellow or greenish yellow with narrow dark brown stripes on the edge of the sternites and pseudosutures. Evaporatorium with a mesial black spot. Lateral margin of the abdomen with a green stripe corresponding to ventral part of connexivum. Antennae yellow to orange. Legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" startId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" targetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1874,1988]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1874,1896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Fernandes &amp; Nascimento &amp; Nunes, 2018" authorityName="Fernandes &amp; Nascimento &amp; Nunes" authorityYear="2018" box="[281,447,1874,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Pygoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amianta" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[281,447,1874,1896]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">Pygoda amianta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[454,510,1874,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[454,510,1874,1895]" pageId="4" pageNumber="209">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
Head. Not punctured dorsally. Mandibular plates laterally yellow to orange with parallel black line, inner margin sometimes yellow (
<figureCitation box="[455,559,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[262,1368,199,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[196,1390,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–B; Pygoda variegata sp. n. C–D; Pygoda poecila sp. n. E–F; Pygoda irrorata G–H; Pygoda polita I–J; Pygoda ramosa sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460050/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Margin of the tylus dark brown. Ventral surface greenish yellow. First rostral segment clearly surpassing bucculae in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
Thorax. Pronotum densely punctured, punctures concolorous and shallow; cicatrices, delimiting furrows and surrounding calloused stripes concolorous with pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[833,940,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[262,1368,199,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[196,1390,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–B; Pygoda variegata sp. n. C–D; Pygoda poecila sp. n. E–F; Pygoda irrorata G–H; Pygoda polita I–J; Pygoda ramosa sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460050/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
), without spots or punctures. Anterolateral margin yellow or reddish; line of concolorous fine punctures short, not reaching ¼ of the margin. Scutellum with fine concolorous punctures sparser on anterior half than on remaining parts, anterior punctures slightly bigger than posterior punctures. Corium with all veins yellow. Propleura with dark stripe alongside dark, fine and dense punctures; green line parallel to yellow margin. Evaporatorium concolorous and slightly rugose with dark spots. Peritreme long reaching 2/3 of the distance between ostiole of the scent gland and margin of the body. Metasternal process greenish yellow with arms broad and receiving fourth and most of third rostral segment (
<figureCitation box="[1236,1339,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[262,1368,199,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[196,1390,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–B; Pygoda variegata sp. n. C–D; Pygoda poecila sp. n. E–F; Pygoda irrorata G–H; Pygoda polita I–J; Pygoda ramosa sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460050/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
Abdomen. Connexivum with sparse tiny concolorous punctures; excavated areas concolorous; base of lateral spines green. Lateral part of segment VII, corresponding to ventral side of connexivum, pale yellow with margin black. Area around spiracles green. Rounded black spots close to spiracles on each segment (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1296,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1969,1991]" captionTargetBox="[262,1368,199,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[196,1390,193,1950]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 12. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–B; Pygoda variegata sp. n. C–D; Pygoda poecila sp. n. E–F; Pygoda irrorata G–H; Pygoda polita I–J; Pygoda ramosa sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460050/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[271,405,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1372,483,1866]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Figs. 1A–C</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with posterolateral angles flattened and slightly projected posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1422,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1372,483,1866]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of the genital cup small, elliptical and narrow. Paramere with posterior processes directed dorsally, small and digitiform; distal process longer than dorsal (
<figureCitation box="[885,973,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1372,483,1866]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); dorsal margin flat or gently excavated. Proctiger brown, long, level with posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[790,922,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1372,483,1866]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Figs 1A, C</figureCitation>
); lateral excavation forming dorsally a small crest; posterior face dorsally tumid. Ventral rim dark brown with expansions slightly developed and not tumid (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1372,483,1866]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface mostly unicolor except by a suffused medial longitudinal stripe; punctures coarse and dark. Phallus short, ventral expansion slightly bitumid (
<figureCitation box="[709,812,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1749,1771]" captionTargetBox="[204,1388,317,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[176,1410,295,1744]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 10. Phallus: A—Hypoxys sp.; B—Pygoda amianta sp. n.; C—Pygoda variegata sp. n.; D—Pygoda poecila sp. n.; E—Pygoda irrorata; F—Pygoda polita; G—Pygoda ramosa sp. n.; H—Pygoda expolita (ph—phallus; ves—vesica. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460048/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
Female (
<figureCitation box="[298,389,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[251,1330,564,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[220,1372,483,1866]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pygoda amianta sp. n. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates. (pyg—pygophore; dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; gp—genital superior process; paparameres; gc8—gonocoxite 8; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la8—laterotergite 8; la9—laterotergite 9; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460030/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 1D</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites 8 with lateral margin arched, posterior margin straight and dark; punctuation dark concentrated on inner half; sutural border contiguous; gonapophysis 8 not visible. Gonocoxites 9 narrow; distal margin straight. Laterotergites 8 with distal margin black; slightly below the level of segment VII. Laterotergites 9 with basal part flat; black apices clearly below the level of laterotergites 8. Capsula seminalis globose with processes short, barely exceeding anterior annular flange, and uniform in length (
<figureCitation box="[1232,1335,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1864,1886]" captionText="FIGURE 11. Internal female: A—Hypoxys sp.; B—Pygoda amianta sp. n.; C—Pygoda variegata sp. n.; D—Pygoda poecila sp. n.; E—Pygoda irrorata; F—Pygoda polita; G—Pygoda ramosa sp. n.; H—Pygoda expolita (aaf—anterior annular flange; ch—chitinellipsen; cs—capsula seminalis; dr—ductus receptaculi; gc9—gonocoxite 9; la9—laterotergite 9; paf—posterior annular flange; pc—pars communis; pi—pars intermedialis; tdr—thickening of ductus receptaculi; tvi—thickening of vaginal intima; x—abdominal segment X. Scale = 1mm)." pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Ductus receptaculi (tdr) short, slightly longer than capsula seminalis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1221]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1124,1149]" pageId="5" pageNumber="210">Comments.</emphasis>
The reddish color of the pronotal margins is very striking but not all specimens examined show this color, maybe it is only a variation of the yellow.
</paragraph>
